Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives - Season 18, Episode 3




Servin' Up San Francisco

This trip, Guy's cruisin' the San Francisco coast for a diverse culinary road trip. First, Guy swings by a NY-style deli crankin' out old-fashioned chicken noodle with matzo ball soup and potato latkes. Then, he's off to San Fran's food truck park, where the reinvented Japanese/Korean truck hooks Guy up with a totally unique take on Asian-fusion in the pork belly and short rib kojas. And the food extravaganza ends at a repurposed garage in the Mission District for some southern hospitality served up in braised beef short ribs and spicy shrimp and gravy.




Original Air Date: 09-Sep-2013
